{
  "_comment_architecture": [
    "Multi-source EPCIS 2.0 supply-chain trail assembling one Fjordline Aurora Shell garment (01/09521234003007/21/AUR-2026-000001).",
    "Chained TransformationEvents across four sites — spinning (rPET fibre -> yarn) at the spinning mill, weaving (yarn + merino -> greige fabric) at the weaving mill, dyeing/laminating (greige -> 3-layer laminate) at the dyeing house, and cut-and-sew (laminate -> finished garment) at the cut-and-sew facility — then commissioning (ADD) and shipping. Each step's site is an EPCIS readPoint (source dimension), consistent with granularity = Model/Batch/Item only; the ilmd stamps the batch lot the garment is created into.",
    "Intermediate materials use GTIN+lot Digital Links; all identifiers use the 952 demo prefix with valid mod-10 check digits.",
    "HTTP header: GS1-Extensions: oec=https://ref.openepcis.io/extensions/common/core/,eutex=https://ref.openepcis.io/extensions/eu/textile/",
    "See: extensions/common/core/docs/EPCIS_MASTERDATA_AND_EXTENSIONS.md"
  ],
